I really enjoyed this DVD. While twerking was not new to me and I pretty much had the basic standing twerks down, I always wanted to learn how to do wall and ground twerks better. I think that this DVD can be used by someone who has never twerked in their life to those who like myself knows how to twerk but would like to learn more intermediate to advance moves. I hope they come out with another DVD.

Not sure if I will ever twerk for anyone but, I CAN now if I want to. I feel empowered, I JUST LEARNED A NEW TRICK. It is an experience to be tried for both women and MEN.

I just got my video today and after reviewing it, it is everything I thought it would be! Easy to follow instructions and fun music to work out too.

Here are the reasons this video gets 5 Stars:
#1 - Legit twerkers. There are plenty of twerk tutorials on YouTube, and they're all fun, but not all instructors are equal if you're really trying to get professional or just super good with it. This video has more proper technique and style than others I've dabbled with.
#2 - Step-by-step instruction. Kelsey and Kendra break it down really nicely so you can focus on practicing/drilling specific movements.
#3 - Covers several variations, so you learn enough moves to put together  a good freestyle once you get the technique down.
#4 - Good production values.
#5 - A section that emphasizes style.

I'm very pleased with this purchase!

I recieved the item on time, so the seller is reliable.  The video is pretty good and is quite in a bit of detail, however I was kinda hoping each section of the video would be longer. The girls in the video have such a charming personalities that doesn't feel forced at all and seem to enjoy what they are doing.  One of the reasons I went a head and ordered the video. However after each section of the video you go back to the main menu which is kinda a hassle but not that bad. My biggest complaint is the price. I feel that this is a twenty dollar purchase not a thirty dollar one.
